## 4. Content to Preserve or Reflect

- **Hero quote (Pat Conroy):** Already on new site; keep Italian or offer both.
- **Secondary quote:** "Ogni cento metri il mondo cambia." (Roberto Bolaño) — use in CTAs or editorial.
- **Form informazioni:** Contact form with GDPR-compliant fields: Nome e cognome, Email, Telefono WhatsApp, Oggetto, Messaggio, Consenso WhatsApp (GDPR).
- **Cookie / Privacy:** Legacy uses a cookie alert and GDPR (Reg. UE 2016/679); new site must have cookie consent and privacy policy and link them where appropriate.
- **Footer credits:** "Sito web realizzato da DGMSUPPORTO" (optional to keep); "Copyright © [year] Travelland SRL - Agenzia di viaggi Milano. Tutti i diritti riservati."
- **Joomla notice:** Remove (legacy CMS); new site is Next.js.

---

## 5. Revamp Goals (New Site)

- **Tech:** Next.js (App Router), design system (`.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`), responsive, accessible.
- **Content:** Same business and legal info; improved UX, clearer hierarchy, modern visuals (hero, destination cards, featured package, testimonials).
- **Tours:** Prossimi viaggi / Storico Viaggi represented as cards and detail flows (e.g. Egypt, Iceland, Sri Lanka, Naples–Salerno–Amalfi) with clear CTAs (View Details, Inquire, WhatsApp).
- **Trust:** P.IVA, codice univoco, sede legale, reception hours, and GDPR wording visible where appropriate (footer, contact, form).

---

## 6. Checklist for New Pages or Content

- [ ] Contact details (email, phones, WhatsApp) match section 2.
- [ ] Legal/fiscal (P.IVA, codice univoco, sede) in footer or contact.
- [ ] Reception hours and "su appuntamento" stated where relevant.
- [ ] Forms mention GDPR and link to privacy policy; consent checkboxes where required.
- [ ] Navigation aligns with legacy structure (section 3) unless product decision says otherwise.
- [ ] No references to Joomla or old CMS; no outdated "Site description here..." placeholders.
